articles.author: Prak Chan Thul
articles.description: Cambodians voted on Sunday in a one-sided election certain to prolong the ruling party's dominance of politics, clearing the path for a historic leadership transition and the end of the reign of one of the world's longest-serving premiers.
articles.title: Cambodia holds lopsided election before historic transfer of power

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A wildfire which has raged on the Greek island of Rhodes for six days forced thousands of tourists and island residents to shelter in schools and indoor stadiums on Sunday after they were evacuated from coastal villages and resorts.
articles.title: Tourists flee Greek island Rhodes wildfire, thousands evacuated

articles.author: Maayan Lubell
articles.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu was fitted with a pacemaker on Sunday after experiencing a heart arrhythmia, and was under observation in the cardiac ward of a Tel Aviv-area hospital, his doctors said.
articles.title: Israel's Netanyahu in hospital after getting pacemaker

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China will resume 15-day visa-free entry for citizens of Singapore and Brunei from Wednesday, its embassies in the two countries said, more than three years after the visas were suspended to stop the spread of COVID-19.
articles.title: China to resume 15-day visa-free entry for Singapore, Brunei citizens

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Top Chinese diplomat Wang Yi proposed high-level talks between China, Japan and South Korea in a meeting with the Japanese foreign minister in Indonesia this month, Kyodo news agency reported on Sunday.
articles.title: Top Chinese diplomat proposes talks with Japan, South Korea - Kyodo

articles.author: Emma Farge, Brenna Hughes Neghaiwi
articles.description: The Treaty of Lausanne that formed modern Turkey is still cherished by some but remains a disappointment for others including Kurds and Armenians who hoped for autonomous regions and justice for Ottoman-era crimes.
articles.title: Treaty that created modern Turkey still evokes pain for some, 100 years after signing

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: United States Navy personnel from a newly commissioned U.S. combat ship paraded through Australia's capital on Sunday, as the two allies carry out war games amid China's military build-up in the region.
articles.title: USS Canberra personnel parade in Australia capital amid joint war games

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A Russian air attack on Ukraine's southern port of Odesa early on Sunday killed one, injured nearly 20 and badly damaged an Orthodox cathedral, Ukrainian officials said, adding the icon of the patroness of the city had been retrieved from under the rubble.
articles.title: Russian attack on Odesa kills one, damages cathedral, Ukrainian officials say

articles.author: Nadja Wohlleben
articles.description: Prominent German LGBTQ+ rights activist Anastasia Biefang has expressed concerns about an increase in homophobic and anti-transgender violence and abuse in the country, comparing it to rhetoric used by the Nazis.
articles.title: German LGBTQ+ activist warns over 'worrying' hate crime rise
